So its been a while since I last wrote anything in here...and why is that you ask?  Well, could it be that I finally have a distraction strong enough to keep me from writing sappy messages at 2:00 in the morning.  That it is.  So I know you all probably are wanting details which I will be glad to talk about how awesome he is whenever ur interested, though I'm not gonna dish too much online cause I wouldn't want him getting too big an ego, now would I?  But yeah, I have pretty much been spending the majority of my time hanging out and getting to know him.  Which has been so much fun.  Its nice to have finally found a guy worth getting to know.  And its weird cause I never would have thought of myself as someone to actually get "picked up" in a random place...but we met in an elevator.  And me being my usual self was totally oblivious to the fact that I was getting hit on until about our 3rd date.  Go me for being the perceptive sales person.  lol  Anyways, he's incredibly funny, very sweet, very generous..if ya know what i mean? ;), i feel 100% comfortable around him...and he is about by far the most stable person I have ever been interested in.  Which for those of you who know my dating history...I could make fund a psychiatric practice off the issues of those other guys.  So yeah.  I can say for the first time in a looooooong while that I am genuinely happy and I dunno whether that is because of him, or because something about me has changed in meeting him, but I have absolutely no complaints.  Well, gotta get back to work so I can leave here at a decent time.  So catch you all later.
Could it be that my luck is changing?  I'm starting to get that feeling....more details to come later....

What is it about the rain that inevitably leaves me sitting alone with the lights turned low, listening to sad country songs and pondering life?  I for once would like that euphoria I always feel driving down the road in the sunlight with the fresh air blowing in to carry over to everyday.  But alas...still no one to come home to but the cat...and a list full of errands to do...

But hey...when life throws you lemons...make lemonade....and then market the hell out of it so you can increase your gross margins.

Oh, and I feel as if I should clarify what exactly "Anti-Valentines' Day" entails for those of you who would like to join in the festivities worldwide:

1 - you must go to the grocery store and specifically buy yourself some little delicacy you wouldn't otherwise make for yourself.

2 - wear your most comfortable pair of clothes...after all...today is all about you.

3 - watch that movie that always makes you feel better whether it be Bridget Jones or Rambo.  

4 - Pamper yourself...I prefer a pedicure or a seaweed mask.  Guys - don't be ashamed to go super metro today.  

and FINALLY!

5 - Sit happy...knowing that if you want to express your feelings to someone, you don't need to wait til a random day in February to do it.  Honestly. I'd rather get a daisy you picked on the side of the road that you gave me just for the heck of it than an overpriced bouquet of flowers that you felt obligated to give me because of all of the 1-800-flowers and hallmark commercials that have been on tv all day.  

So, i'm sure you're thinking...oh, she's just the bitter jilted lover.  Well, yes, i've been dumped twice on Valentine's Day...but anyone who knows me will say once a hopeless romantic, always a hopeless romantic.  I'm still waiting for that white horse to come breaking through the woods....:-D

So its official...my mondays are pretty soon going to be sucked up by the Dale Carnegie sales course.  I am soooo excited.  Not only is this going to be an excellent work training experience for me, I really think I am going to learn a lot from it.  Unfortunately what that means is...homework.  On a side note, I've decided to start looking for a place I can take arabic classes.  if anyone has suggestions, please let me know and if anyone would like to take it with me, that would be cool too.  Languages are always easier with a companion to study with.

OK, My weekend has just been topped off by the fact that Jurassic Park is coming on tv.  not that I don't have the entire film series on DVD and could watch it anytime, the fact that its coming on on its own makes it not so pitiful that this marks the probably 50th time or so i've seen it.  I don't think my passion for paleontology/archaeology will ever die.  There's something about the past that's so hypnotizing.  Learning about it somehow makes everything make sense.  Anyways, its starting so enough babbling for me.  

OH, and does anyone want to join me tomorrow in my protest of Valentine's day and the useless commerce driven enhancement of the loneliness of every single person around the world?  I'm up for anything.

So I by and far had the best time last night.  It was the first time me and ALL my girls have gotten together.  We had such an awesome time and I must say its nice having a friend studying massage therapy that needs a "dummy" to practice on.  Man...i'll volunteer for that anytime.  So yeah, all in all it was a great weekend.  Had a lot of fun friday just hangin out, watching movies with my fellow scene it lover.  So I guess its back to the grind again.  I always dread sundays...you can see all the work you have for the week and that just sort of ruins the whole experience.  Eh, what can ya do?  Well, i think i am going to read some more of my crichton book and maybe get to bed early.  I didn't get to sleep in like I usually do on the weekends so I could use the rest.  Hope everyone else's weekends were awesome.  Catch y'all later.

So I was driving home last night in the car and heard this song again which got me thinking about things.  For some reason this has become a topic that keeps coming up lately so I think that's why its been on my mind so much when it normally isn't.  I can't help but wonder how things would have turned out and what my life and even myself would be like if things had gone differently that day.  If i'd just decided to stay home or go to bed early.  I have never had any regrets about anything I've done before and since, but I can't help but wonder what it would be like...to not have ever felt so much hurt...to not feel like I always have to take charge of my life.  It was nice just letting things ride...living on this idealized dream that I never had any doubts that would happen and that I knew was the one thing I wanted out of life.  So now here I am.  Somehow I managed to eek out and get that dream, but it doesn't really mean the same thing anymore that it did before.  I am here, but I don't really feel a sense of accomplishment.  I dunno if that makes any sense.  But I still feel like i'm missing something.  I just don't know what it is...

So I randomly decided to join a community like a week ago and met someone who was just looking for someone to hang out with.  After spending 3 hrs playing scene it in my apartment getting liquored up...he has shown his true nature as the obscure movie king.  I swear, if they made some B horror flick in the 1960s this guy's seen it.  Of course I got all the 80s stoner movies right and most of the chick flicks, but hey...that about sums up my lifetime...lol.  In the end, I won by 1 question.  We were neck in neck the whole time.  I know you guys are prolly thinking i am the biggest dork in the world, but that was by far the funnest internet meeting i've ever had.  Most of them end up being either stalkers or losers.  I must say it was quite refreshing.  Anyways, things are looking up at work.  I hit 110% of my sales goal with 4 more days in the sales month to go.  WOOHOO.  I think i might finally be getting the hang of this shit.  Plus, now my boss won't be riding my ass til friday.  Which is always a good thing.  That man could give the pope a heart attack.  Anyways, i think its time for me to go to bed.  I am exhausted..thanks to a "distraction" that kept me up last night...but hey...who's complaining?  I'm certainly not.  ;)  Laters.

Why is it that guys you want to be interested in you never call and the ones you wish would go away can't stop calling/writing/e-mailing.  Sad thing is, I sort of like the attention...which is a bad thing cause this person has the never ending potential to stir things up in my life again.  Which considering my current boredom, might be a welcomed diversion.  I think he is going to come on vacation with me and the girls this spring which means I have to get my ass back into shape again.  At least back to where I was when we were dating.  Its always welcoming to have a motivation point to work out.  Well, I guess I should get started cooking some dinner and then working on my pricing proposals for tomorrow.  Night all.

So. It has once again been a while since I have written. Work just isn't leaving much time for anything else. So what to update about. I finally am a commissioned salesperson so my salary should take a huuuuge leap this year. I love my apartment and might be moving in with Jen soon if things work out with her finding a job here in Virginia Beach. Since I can't think of anything else monumental that has happened since last time i wrote...here are some....QUIZZES!!!!

OK.  SO i know i havent written in a looong while.  But its beena busy few weeks.  Let me start off by saying...thank you Paull's Deli and Jagermeister for bringing me together with 2 of the coolest guys I have ever met.  Its been a great few weeks and many more to come hopefully.
